Dissolve the gelatin in the boiling water. Mix in the cold water and set aside. Mix and bake cake as directed for one 9x13 inch pan. Let cake cool for 20 to 25 minutes. Poke holes in cake about 1 inch apart. Pour gelatin into holes and over the top of the cake. Refrigerate cake while making the topping. Mix instant pudding, whipped topping mix and milk until stiff. Frost cake and store in refrigerator.